cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.NE 

This paper deals with a machine learning technique, Kernel Principal Component Analysis (KPCA), and its approximation methods for classification tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as these fields heavily rely on dimensionality reduction techniques. The paper also involves the evaluation of these methods on real-world datasets, indicating a focus on practical applications, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
